<td id="title_text"><h1><a title="SuperATM" class="currentChild" href="SuperATM">SuperATM</a></h1></td>



</tr></table>
</td>
</tr></table></div>



<div id="content" class="content wikipage" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<p id="l1">
An <a title="Extension" href="Extension">extension</a> to the <a title="Adobe Type Manager" href="Adobe_Type_Manager">Adobe Type Manager</a> utility that is distinguished by its ability to imitate fonts not available in a particular system. If, for example, a document contains text originally set in Caslon, and it is opened on a system that does not contain Caslon, SuperATM uses <a title="Multiple Master" href="Multiple_Master">multiple master</a> technology to create an ersatz Caslon which, though perhaps differing slightly from true Caslon, will posses the proper character widths. As a result, the layout of the document will not change. 
</p>
